                    <h3 class="mb-3">Web Design & Development</h3>
                    <p>In 2023, Image Pointe managed just 11 WordPress WooCommerce websites and had not yet adopted a standardized approach to web accessibility, 
                        limiting the scalability of its e-commerce platform. After joining the company, I developed a reusable Oxygen Builder 
                        framework featuring integrated USPS/UPS shipping APIs, automated inventory imports, customizable checkout fields, and built-in 
						Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 Level AA accessibility improvements. I also managed hosting and DNS 
						services on Cloudflare and WP Engine, as well as performance optimization and ongoing maintenance across all client stores.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        As a result, the time required to launch new webstores was reduced from five days to approximately 12 hours, and the <b>SEO performance 
						improved by 42% within a single year after implementing accessibility best practices</b>. This enabled the company to grow its e-commerce 
						platform to more than <b>50 online stores</b> by 2025, serving international and local labor unions, including Starbucks Workers United, 
						AFL-CIO, and UAW.
                    </p>
