					<!--Digital Accessibility Audits Portfolio-->
                    <h3 class="mb-3">Digital Accessibility Audits</h3>
                        <p>In early 2026, Reliable Property Solutions LLC engaged Patterson Pixel to perform a comprehensive accessibility audit of its 
						website to evaluate conformance with Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA success criteria in support of ADA Title III 
						accessibility considerations. I conducted both manual and automated testing across all seven pages of the website on desktop and mobile 
						devices, <b>identifying 39 accessibility issues</b>. I then delivered a detailed report outlining each issue along with prioritized remediation 
						recommendations to help the client improve accessibility, reduce barriers for users with disabilities, and align the website with 
						recognized accessibility standards.
                        </p>
					<br>
					<br>
					<!--Business Technology Solutions Portfolio-->
                    <h3 class="mb-3">Business Technology Solutions</h3>
                        <p>In 2025, The Restoration Project contacted Patterson Pixel after recurring errors in their Zapier automation disrupted customer order 
							processing between their WordPress WooCommerce website and Flodesk email marketing system. I traced the issue to the automation using 
							product names as identifiers, which caused conflicts between similarly named products. I resolved the problem by switching the 
							workflow to use unique Product IDs, adding error handling for existing customers in Flodesk, and creating a step-by-step technical 
							guide to help staff manage the updated Zapier workflow. The successful project resulted in a reliable, long-term solution and an 
							ongoing client relationship, with The Restoration Project returning for <b>two additional contracts in 2026</b>.
                        </p>
